snippet.textDisplay: I like how Skip tries to say “well Mahomes lost to Tennessee...hmmmm.” He always sounds like that typical fan who assumes record determines everything in sports. What he must’ve forgot (or stubbornly doesn’t admit) is that KC lost that game because of a bad call to punt the ball on a 4th and short with just over 5 minutes left in the game. MAHOMES NEVER SAW THE FIELD AFTER THAT PUNT BECAUSE THE DEFENSE COULDN’T GET OFF OF THE FIELD. That happened in the AFC Conference Championship last year, against Houston earlier this year, against the Colts this year, and against the Chargers last year. If you are like Skip and assume that “defenses have figured out Mahomes” or “Mahomes is a one-and-done”, just remember the only strategy that has worked on beating Mahomes is keeping him off of the field. That’s it! If you can keep Mahomes off of the field, you have a shot at beating KC. Sorry for my rant but I hate “analyzers” like Skip.
